Consider the molecule in blue bound to a binding site. Identify the binding interactions taking place at ii shown in red. <image 1>

A. hydrogen bonds
B. ionic bonds
C. van der Waals interactions

The interaction labeled "ii" in the image shows a dashed line connecting a positively charged nitrogen (NH3+) and a negatively charged oxygen (O2-). This type of interaction is characteristic of an ionic bond, where there is an electrostatic attraction between oppositely charged ions.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

B. ionic bonds
